---
import RadhaPhoto from "../assets/Radha-photo.jpg";
import Resume from "../assets/Radha-Resume.pdf";
---

<section
  class="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-6 md:gap-8 py-16 md:py-20 px-6 md:px-0"
  id="about"
>
  <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-2 reveal">
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold section-heading">About Me</h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--text-color)] text-sm">My introduction</p>
  </div>
  <div class="w-full flex flex-col md:grid md:grid-cols-[0.6fr_1fr] gap-8 md:gap-10 items-start">
    <div class="w-full max-w-[250px] md:max-w-none md:w-full h-[240px] md:h-[320px] reveal-left relative mx-auto">
      <img
        src={RadhaPhoto.src}
        alt="Radha Rani"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover rounded-2xl brightness-110 contrast-105 about-img"
      />
      <div class="absolute -bottom-2 -right-2 w-full h-full border-2 border-[var(--first-color-lighter)] rounded-2xl -z-10"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-[var(--text-color)] reveal-right">
      <p class="text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
        My path to software development started in supply chain analysis — where
        I developed a strong analytical, data-driven mindset and learned to solve
        complex problems at scale. Working closely with clients at Accenture
        sharpened my understanding of user needs and what it truly takes to
        deliver experiences people love.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
        What drew me to software engineering was the ability to bring imagination
        and creativity to life — to take an idea and turn it into something real,
        beautiful, and useful. I earned my Software Engineering diploma from
        BrainStation, and my team won <strong class="text-[var(--title-color)]">first place</strong>
        in the BrainStation × Microsoft hackathon for Co-Teacher, an AI-powered
        tool built to make a real impact.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
        What drives me is knowing real people use what I build every day. I bring
        creativity, analytical thinking, and a genuine care for the user into
        everything I ship. I use AI tools like GitHub Copilot, Claude, and Cursor
        daily — not as a shortcut, but to stay focused on building things that
        actually matter.
      </p>

      <!-- Stats + buttons row -->
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 md:gap-6 mt-1 flex-wrap">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <i class="uil uil-briefcase-alt text-lg text-[var(--first-color)]"></i>
          <span class="font-bold text-[var(--title-color)]">2+</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-[var(--text-color)]">Years Exp.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <i class="uil uil-folder-open text-lg text-[var(--first-color)]"></i>
          <span class="font-bold text-[var(--title-color)]">4+</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-[var(--text-color)]">Projects</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <i class="uil uil-trophy text-lg text-[var(--first-color)]"></i>
          <span class="font-bold text-[var(--title-color)]">1st</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-[var(--text-color)]">Hackathon</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-3 items-center flex-wrap mt-1">
        <a
          class="bg-[var(--first-color-alt)] px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-white w-fit cursor-pointer flex items-center gap-2 btn-hover font-medium text-sm"
          href="./Radha-Resume.pdf"
          download
        >
          Download CV <i class="uil uil-download-alt"></i>
        </a>
        <a
          href="#contact"
          class="px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg border-2 border-[var(--first-color-alt)] text-[var(--first-color-alt)] w-fit cursor-pointer flex items-center gap-2 btn-hover font-medium hover:bg-[var(--first-color-alt)] hover:text-white transition-colors duration-300 text-sm"
        >
          Let's Talk <i class="uil uil-message"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
